latestPosts.caption:
Grateful 🙏 I’ve never asked God for anything, yet He has given me more than I ever imagined.

I’ve taken risks without overanalyzing. Bet on things that made 0 sense on paper. Walked into the unknown with nothing but faith.

And every single time, something clicked. Something worked out. Not by chance, not by luck—but by something far greater than my own plans 🤗

I just kept moving, kept doing the right things, and He kept blessing me in ways I never expected—my loving family, incredible friends, boAt, SharkTankIndia, and the overwhelming love from all of you ❤️

I never asked for these gifts. I only believed that as long as I kept walking in the right direction humbly, everything would work out!

So when you think no one is watching, He is.
When you feel unseen, He sees it all 👀

Another year older, another year wiser—protected, guided, and endlessly grateful 🙏🧿

Hum bhi bana lenge, in this new India. 🇮🇳 We Entrepreneurs today are not only building brands, we are building and inspiring a nation that thinks entrepreneurship is cool.

Thank you Hon PM Mr Modi @narendramodi for presenting me with the “Celebrity Entrepreneur of the year”. It’s like a dream come true to receive this award from our hon PM, I still can’t believe that I shared the stage with you Sir and I won this award; thank you India for voting for me. I am honored to be a part of this category with such amazing nominees including @sadhguru @katrinakaif @chetri_sunil11 @thenameisyash @kanganaranaut , you are all winners in your own right …. Can’t believe it but thank you India. 
🇮🇳 🇮🇳🇮🇳❤️❤️❤️

Keep Dreaming. Keep Hustling. Stay Humble.

A golden era led by legends like Virat and Rohit are gently passing the torch… They gave us memories, pride, and belief. 

Now, a new story begins, one of youth, hunger, and fearless ambition.Captain Shubman Gill takes the helm, with rising stars like Yashasvi stepping into the spotlight. Wishing all the best to the new Captain of Indian test cricket. 🇮🇳 

A new dawn for Indian cricket and we’re here for it. Because in the end… that’s how life moves. Change is never easy. It tough, emotional, and uncertain. But is it necessary.. Absolutely…Because without change, there is no growth.

latestPosts.caption:
18 years.

So many memes. So many meltdowns.

And finally... so much magic.

RCB didn’t just win, belief did.

Pain. Patience. Payoff. God’s plan. 

And we were right there when it happened. ⛵️

Truth is - Everyone sucks. Not just You. 

Some quietly. Some confidently.
Some in Haryanvi. Some in Queen’s English.
But trust me …. we all suck….

In 2016, I was walking around Delhi with boAt cables in my bag, pitching in the heat, getting rejected 8 out of 10 times. I smiled. Stayed. Sold anyway🤷🏻‍♂️. Today, some of these stores now have a boAt hoarding.

So next time your brain says “Don’t do it, you suck”…

Remind it:
That’s not a reason to stop.
That’s just the standard human experience.

#EveryoneSucksNotJustYou✌🏻

latestPosts.caption:
It’s not every day that the government asks founders to dream bigger.

But at Startup Mahakumbh, that’s exactly what happened. I was there. I heard the full speech. Hon. Minister @piyushgoyalofficial Ji isn’t against founders. He believes in us.His point was simple: India has come far, but to lead the world…we need to aim higher.

It reminded me of something I say often on Shark Tank India, If you want to build a world-class product, you must know your competition.That applies to India too.

Benchmarking against China, the US, or anyone else — isn’t weakness. It’s smart strategy. We’re already the 3rd largest startup ecosystem in the world and the fastest-growing major economy 🇮🇳

But if we want to be No.1 — We need to also go deep into AI, deeptech, climate, mobility, infra. We need LLMs and innovation stacks that compete on global standards.

And to make that happen, we also need Scientific risk, More patient capital, Founder–policymaker collaboration and a long-term national vision. 🤝

Kyunki jab sapne bade hote hain, toh kadam bhi bade uthane padte hain 🙏

So, yes, what we’ve built is incredible.
But what we can build… is far greater.

Let’s get to work 🔥
